    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-03-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-03-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="541"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d541">
                <head>541. Telegram 1769 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d541fn1">Source:
                        Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/3–1956. Confidential; Priority;
                        Limit Distribution. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_CRN_1"
                            >Clough</persName>; cleared by Phleger in substance and by <persName
                            corresp="#p_MWP_1">McConaughy</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1956-03-19">March 19, 1956, 6:21 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d541-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d541-1"/>
                <p>1769. For <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>At March 22 meeting follow guidance given Department’s 1751.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Telegraphing separately for your background reports Secretary’s
                        conversations in New Delhi Taipei and Tokyo.</item>
                    <pb facs="0914" n="867" type="typeset" xml:id="pg_867"/>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Also telegraphing separately for your background report on Grand Jury
                        investigations New York and San Francisco into passport frauds among persons
                        Chinese race since <persName corresp="#p_WP_1">Wang</persName> might seize
                        this as pretext charge persecution Chinese in US.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>Return soon Spielman history of talks to date with your suggested
                        revisions as this might be required on short notice if Communists broke off
                        or carried out threat publish complete record.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HH_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Hoover</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
